            <documentation type="Summary">WATCH-Forcing-Data-ERA-Interim (WFDEI) was produced post-WATCH using WFD methodology applied to ERA-Interim data. It is a meteorological forcing dataset extending into early 21st C (1979 – 2012). WFDEI dataset (version 18th September 2013; http://www.eu-watch.org/data_availability) is provided for bona fide research purposes only. No warranty is given as to their suitability for user applications. No liability is accepted by the authors for any errors or omissions in the data or associated information and/or documentation.</documentation>
            <documentation type="Source">Data downloaded from the ftp server ftp://ftp.iiasa.ac.at/ on 15/06/2015 and stored in the User Data Gateway (UDG) of the Santander MetGroup climate services (http://meteo.unican.es/en/dataservices). Daily minimum and maximum temperatures have been obtained from the 3-hourly temperature. 3-hourly relative humidity has been obtained from the 3-hourly surface pressure, mean temperature and specific humidity and then aggregrated to obtain the daily mean, minimum and maximum values.</documentation>
			<documentation type="Terms of use">Dataset included in the User Data Gateway (UDG, http://www.meteo.unican.es/udg-wiki) maintained by the Santander MetGroup. Register and accept the data policy to access to this dataset.</documentation>
